<tableCitation id="B129C87EA6C2FEC822B04D35FC9A157A" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. K 2 P distances between DNA barcode sequences of Aureopterix species. GenBank accession numbers are appended to each sample." pageId="5" pageNumber="34">1</tableCitation>
) We recovered only the COI-1a fragment (325bp) for both samples. In the best scoring RAxML-tree the genus 
<taxonomicName id="F8B8368E8B0B473D6B46BD3DDA4ABA54" authority="Gibbs, 2010" authorityName="Gibbs" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Micropterigidae" genus="Aureopterix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aureopterix" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6E1D36E36EE848B942A26689BA28215A" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Aureopterix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well supported as a monophylum with respect to 
<taxonomicName id="ED9B309031233121C85CE5F4FB4FCD29" authorityName="Gibbs" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Micropterigidae" genus="Zealandopterix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zealandopterix" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AC863AFD9D58BFD9FA2AF13EAB462006" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Zealandopterix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D5A2D65C712B71CCADFD2156DEBFEB6F" authorityName="Gibbs" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Micropterigidae" genus="Tasmantrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tasmantrix" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0A840C7FE3267C59EF7E473439DCA7AC" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Tasmantrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="AE8C657C7EB9AA3C91324AB2ED7ACB82">BS</collectionCode>
= 97). Relationships among 
<taxonomicName id="3AF455E1EB0883C74B4BEF6C29F15F01" class="Insecta" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. bachmaensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bachmaensis">
<emphasis id="1FFE2F50CF364E5B6310C14D9948E9AB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">A. bachmaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="8D1991B979FBF59F43559D362CC59570" class="Insecta" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. micans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis id="18D6FB9BBBB2D9A0E0BBA969660EC218" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">A. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FE47382B2BA93454ABC0807AB651A442" class="Insecta" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. sterops" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sterops">
<emphasis id="19A74798F1F8CC7351530C340F7E71A9" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">A. sterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remain unclear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6A0C291B58B9B188AF70E95790A3B172" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="95636D978B563349174D26C8104E6B30" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C59B7BC6DDD160D354ACA169292CBE1" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
The locality in the Bach-Ma National Park will probably not remain the only record of this new species. Future field work will provide a more accurate picture of the species range, which is probably restricted to the Truong Son Mountain Range (= Annamite Range). This roughly north to south running mountain range along the Laos-Vietnam border is an area of endemism which gained global recognition in the early to mid-1990s with the discovery of six spectacular mammal species (
<bibRefCitation id="2A99F1670EC4F363558E0A3E5776F4AF" author="Sterling, EJ" journalOrPublisher="Bioinformatics" pageId="22" pageNumber="51" refId="B63" refString="Sterling, EJ, Hurley, MM, 2005. Conserving biodiversity in Vietnam: applying biogeography to conservation research. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 56, supplement 1(9): 98-114." title="Conserving biodiversity in Vietnam: applying biogeography to conservation research. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 56, supplement 1 (9): 98 - 114." year="2005">Sterling and Hurley 2005</bibRefCitation>
) that are confined to this range. The report of 
<taxonomicName id="26CEDCA7E62048EDA86DAC03CE9EEA19" class="Insecta" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. bachmaensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bachmaensis">
<emphasis id="EE0BEB82AA191124A7813CE9923DABCB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">A. bachmaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. in the National Park is an example from 
<taxonomicName id="26C74785B0AF36F1B198A9DF35E105C6" class="Insecta" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
underpinning the significance of the area.
</paragraph>
